==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sea snake
<hw>Sea" snake`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of
many species of venomous aquatic snakes of the family
<fam>Hydrophidae</fam>, having a flattened tail and living entirely in
the sea, especially in the warmer parts of the Indian and Pacific
Oceans. They feed upon fishes, and are mostly of moderate size, but some
species become eight or ten feet long and four inches broad.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sea snipe</ent>⟦br⟧
